Installation Manual for A Beautiful Event System
________________________________________
System Requirements
•	Operating System: Windows/Linux/MacOS
•	Web Server: Apache, Nginx, or XAMPP
•	Database: MySQL version 5.7+
•	Programming Languages: PHP 7.4+, HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript
•	Browser: Latest version of Chrome, Firefox, or Edge
•	Dependencies:
o	PHPMyAdmin for database management (optional)
o	Composer (PHP dependency manager)
________________________________________
Installation Steps
1.	Download Project Files
o	Obtain the source code for the A Beautiful Event system. Extract the files into your preferred web server directory:
	For XAMPP: Place files in C:\xampp\htdocs\a_beautiful_event
	For Nginx/Apache/WAXMP: Use the directory /www/html/a_beautiful_event
2.	Create MySQL Database
o	Open PHPMyAdmin or any MySQL client tool.
o	Create a new database using the following SQL command:
CREATE DATABASE a_beautiful_event;
3.	Import Database
o	Open your MySQL interface and select the a_beautiful_event database.
o	Import the provided .sql file:
	Go to Import and upload the a_beautiful_event.sql file.
	Ensure that all tables and initial data are correctly loaded.
4.	Configure Database Connection
o	Navigate to the configuration file (usually  DB.php) and update the connection settings:
define('DB_SERVER', 'localhost');
define('DB_USERNAME', 'your_db_user');
define('DB_PASSWORD', 'your_db_password');
define('DB_NAME', 'a_beautiful_event');
o	Replace your_db_user and your_db_password with your MySQL credentials.
5.	Run the Application
o	Launch your browser and visit:
http://localhost/a_beautiful_event/
