User Manual for A Beautiful Event System
________________________________________
Login and Authentication
1.	Admin Login
o	Access the system through http://localhost/a_beautiful_event/admin.
o	Enter your username and password to log in as an Admin.
2.	Forgot Password
o	If you forget your password, click on the "Forgot Password" link and follow the steps to reset it using your email address.
________________________________________
Dashboard Overview
Upon login, you will be taken to the Admin Dashboard where you can manage various features.
________________________________________
Manage Bookings
1.	View Bookings
o	Navigate the Bookings from the left panel to view all event bookings.
o	You can see the Event Date, Event Type, Venue, and Status.
2.	Add a New Booking
o	Click Add New Booking.
o	Fill out the booking form, including details like Customer Name, Event Type, Service Selection, and Event Date.
3.	Update Booking
o	To update an existing booking, select a booking from the list, click Edit, and modify the necessary details.
________________________________________
Manage Services
1.	Add New Service
o	Go to Services > Add New Service.
o	Enter the service name, description, and price, then save.
2.	Edit/Delete Services
o	To edit or remove a service, select the respective option from the Service List.
________________________________________
Manage Event Types
1.	Add Event Type
o	Navigate to Event Types and click Add New Event Type.
o	Enter the event type name (e.g., Wedding, Concert, etc.).
2.	Delete Event Type
o	Select any event type from the list and click Delete to remove it.
________________________________________
Company Settings
1.	Update Company Information
o	Go to Company Settings and update company details like the name, email, address, and logo.
________________________________________
Permissions and Roles
1.	Manage User Roles
o	In Permissions, you can manage roles such as Superuser, Admin, and User.
o	Assign or remove privileges for creating and updating users, bookings, or bids.
2.	Add New User
o	Navigate to Admin Management > Add New Admin.
o	Enter the admin details, including username, password, and role.
________________________________________
Logout
•	To log out, simply click the Logout button at the top-right of the dashboard.
